Materials Pick-up / Drop-off Tomorrow!!!

On Wednesday, September 2, we will start our weekly materials pick-up and drop-off. This will take place every Wednesday from 2:00-7:00 PM. Tables with the materials will be located in the larger part of the parking lot. The same general area as the first materials pick-up. Tables will be marked by grades. Drop-off boxes will be by class. When exiting your vehicle please make sure you and anyone with you is wearing a mask (school age and up). Please park in a designated parking spot and don‚Äôt block the driving lane.
Please return the forms that were sent out last week. The sooner we can get those back the better. We appreciate your help with this.

post_text:
Good Evening Dunham Families,

Today we completed the 1st day of school for 2020! In true 2020 fashion we started the day off with Zoom having a world-wide tech problem. This affected one class and it was quickly resolved. After that the day went well and the staff was very excited to see our students. We know some had login issues and we are working to help resolve those. We appreciate your patience as we all work our way through this. Congratulations on completing the first day and welcome back everyone! Thank you all for a great start!

Daniel Hoffman
Superintendent / Principal

post_text:
SCHOOL LUNCH PROGRAM INFORMATION

Hello Families,

During distance learning, we will be offering Grab and Go Lunches. Students will need to give their name to receive the meal and each meal will be charged to the student's account. Families are encouraged to complete a Free and Reduced Meal application as soon as possible (see attached). Full price lunches are $4.50 with milk included (if desired). Lunches will have to be pre ordered the week prior. Please fill out our survey (link below) to let us know if you are interested in participating in our Lunch Program. Lunch pick up will be every MONDAY from 12:00 PM-1:00 PM. Please see the attached lunch menu. Lunches will be served in a drive-by or walk up method in front of the Community Room. Every adult and school age student must be wearing a mask in the car or on foot to receive meal service. We will be sending these pre order surveys out weekly.

We apologize for the short notice this week.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc0I5kn0u-Ak_duWwSUy747q_H3kqVJSlVnCXDv8bk_7AT-pQ/viewform?usp=sf_link

post_text:
Materials Pick-up

Hello Dunham Families, our beginning of the school year materials pick-up will be on Wednesday, August 19, from 2:00pm - 7:00pm. It will be a drive through style pick-up. Materials will be divided by grade levels at designated tables. All student items will be clearly marked. Face coverings are required for those picking up the materials.

Teachers will be waving from a distance between 2:00pm - 3:00pm on Wednesday. PTO will also be giving out Otter Pops and popcorn at the end of the drive through between 2:00pm - 3:00pm on Wednesday in a modified version of our Annual Ice Cream Social.

Please remember to wear a mask and follow safety practices.

For those that cannot come to the Wednesday materials pick-up we will be offering a second opportunity on Thursday, August 20, from 4:00pm - 7:00pm. It will be a drive through style pick-up as well.

Please call the office if you have any questions. Have a nice evening.

post_text:
May 28 is the official last day of the school year. We will be having our final pick up and drop off day. Items from students desk, work, projects, awards and reports cards will be available for pick up. Please return all Chromebooks (w/ cords), outstanding work / assignments, textbooks, library books, classroom library books, sports jerseys, or any other items belonging to the school.

Like last time, it will be a ‚Äúgrab-and-go‚Äù approach. Staff will be wearing masks and we ask that you please wear a mask / face covering for the short exchange period while the car window is down. We ask that you pull into the Dunham parking lot and stay to the left as if you were heading towards parent drop off and pick up. Please pull up to the double doors outside of the Community Room.

To prevent overcrowding please follow this pick up / drop off schedule:

8:00-10:00 Last names starting with the letters A-H
10:00-12:00 Last names starting with the letters I-R
12:30-2:30 Last names starting with the letters S-Z

post_text:
Just another reason why Dunham is a special place to go to school.....

Yesterday Mrs. Wilde, Mrs. Schmidt, Mrs. Mohrman, Ms. Brattin, Mrs. Campbell, Mrs. Kidder and Ms. Guthrie made the rounds to our promoting 6th graders‚Äô homes. They delivered smiles, balloons, lawn signs and shirts. The caravan parade included horns, whistles, poster board signs, and decorated cars. It was a heartwarming act and a great way to make our 6th graders feel special. Thank you to all who made this possible. Dunham students and staff are the best!

The staff at Dunham has gone above and beyond what anyone has ever expected of them. Let's show them our gratitude next week during Staff Appreciation Week! Below is an idea for each day, each is a way to show the staff at Dunham how much we care.

On Thursday, join us as we drive in a parade to give our thanks in person! We will meet at the Washoe House and leave together at 4:00pm to wave to our Dunham staff. Please stay in your vehicles unless you would like to send a masked representative to give any gifts to the teachers.

post_text:
Our next learning materials pick up / drop off will be on April 29. Like last time, it will be a ‚Äúgrab-and-go‚Äù approach. Staff will be wearing gloves and masks. We ask that you please wear a mask / facecovernig for the short exchange period while the car window is down. Not all students will have materials to pick up or drop off. Teachers are currently reaching out to their classes to let parents know if there are materials to be picked up or dropped off. If you are unsure please email your child‚Äôs teacher.

To prevent overcrowding please follow this pick up / drop off schedule:

8:00-10:00 Last names starting with the letters A-H
10:00-12:00 Last names starting with the letters I-R
12:30-2:30 Last names starting with the letters S-Z

Also, there were some Flower Power fundraiser items not picked up. They can be picked up this day as well (4/29) unless you have already made other arrangements with Kristin Gabbard.

üå∫Flower Power fundraising materials have arrived! There will be a pick up on Thursday, April 23, from 10:00-11:30am. There are 12 total orders to pick up. Items will be marked and be placed on the red benches directly outside of the office doors. The gates will be open during this time. All you have to do is pull up to the curb, briefly get out of the car and grab your designated item(s). Please wear a mask and follow proper social distancing guidelines.

If for any reason you are unable to make this day, please contact Kristin Gabbard at 415-385-9915 to make arrangements to do a drive-by pick-up in Cotati.

We raised approximately 1500.00 with paper and online sales!! Thank you for continuing to support Dunham and a big thank you to our PTO and Kristin Gabbard.

Meals

I want to bring to your attention that there are several community options for meals for any child ages 0-18. The children do need to be present with the adult picking up the grab-and-go curbside meals.

You can get these curbside meals Mondays through Fridays, 11:00AM-1:00PM at:

Rancho Cotati High School - 5450 Snyder Lane
Technology Middle School - 7165 Burton Avenue
Lawrence Jones Middle School - 5154 Snyder Lane

Other cities like Sebastopol, Santa Rosa, and Petaluma are offering similar programs. Please call the Dunham School Office if you would like more information.

post_text: Dunham School Update
text: Dunham School Update

post_text:
Hello Dunham Families,

I will be taking part in a meeting on Monday, March 16, with the Sonoma County Department of Health Services and the Sonoma County Office of Education. There will be more information to come that I will share within 24 hours after this meeting. Regardless, it seems that a school closure after spring break is highly probable. I share this because I want to give families as much notice as possible so things like childcare can be arranged. These are difficult times and information and protocols seem to change almost daily. Thank you for all of your help and cooperation, stay safe.

Sincerely,

Daniel Hoffman
Superintendent / Principal
Dunham School District
text:
Hello Dunham Families,

I will be taking part in a meeting on Monday, March 16, with the Sonoma County Department of Health Services and the Sonoma County Office of Education. There will be more information to come that I will share within 24 hours after this meeting. Regardless, it seems that a school closure after spring break is highly probable. I share this because I want to give families as much notice as possible so things like childcare can be arranged. These are difficult times and information and protocols seem to change almost daily. Thank you for all of your help and cooperation, stay safe.

Sincerely,

Daniel Hoffman
Superintendent / Principal
Dunham School District
